<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,264,402]" box="[151,254,264,289]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis box="[151,254,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,264,402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The species, recorded as 
<taxonomicName box="[508,630,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scobura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coniata">
<emphasis box="[508,630,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">S. coniata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Huang" box="[682,852,301,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" refString="Huang, B. K. (2001) Fauna of Insects in Fujian Province of China. Volume 4. Fujian Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Fuzhou, China, 165 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Huang (
<number box="[780,843,301,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, was described by Devyatkin in 
<number box="[1257,1316,301,327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
as a new species from Fujian. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[568,644,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scobura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyso">
<emphasis box="[568,644,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">S. lyso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by having the cell spots conjoined and its peculiar horn-shaped juxta.
</paragraph>
